2%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658bfd0bec62ab5daf7ed8ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223423%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20file%20photo%20showing%20a%20game%20of%20Chinese%20chess.%3Cp%3EGonzalo%20Azumendi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Chinese-chess%20champion%20lost%20his%20title%20after%20being%20accused%20of%20showing%C2%A0%26quot%3Bextremely%20bad%20character.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EYan%20Chenglong%2C%2048%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20defecating%20in%20a%20hotel%20bathtub%20after%20winning%20a%20national%20tournament.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20champion%20is%20also%20facing%20accusations%20that%20he%20cheated%20using%20anal%20beads.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Chinese-chess%20champion%20lost%20his%20crown%20after%20being%20accused%20of%20showing%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20bad%20character%26quot%3B%20by%20pooping%20in%20a%20hotel%20bathtub%20as%20he%20celebrated%20his%20title.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYan%20Chenglong%2C%2048%2C%20won%20the%20national%20Chinese-chess%20amateur%20competition%20final%20on%20December%2017%2C%20according%20to%20China's%20state-controlled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globaltimes.cn%2Fpage%2F202312%2F1304337.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20came%20with%20prize%20money%20of%20100%2C000%20yuan%2C%20or%20nearly%20%2414%2C000%2C%20per%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(The%20sport%20is%20not%20quite%20the%20same%20as%20Western%20chess%2C%20and%20is%20also%20known%20by%20its%20Chinese%20name%2C%20Xiangqi.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20checking%20out%20of%20his%20hotel%20the%20next%20day%2C%20an%20employee%20reported%20that%20they%20had%20found%20excrement%20in%20Yan's%20bathtub.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%20fueled%20rumors%20that%20he%20had%20cheated%20in%20the%20tournament%20by%20using%20anal%20beads%20equipped%20with%20wireless%20transmitters%20to%20send%20and%20receive%20information%20to%20a%20computer%20on%20what%20moves%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Anal%20beads%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fchess-feud-hans-niemann-magnus-carlsen-anal-beads-rumor-explained-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20featured%20in%20a%20Western%20chess%20scandal%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20a%20year%20ago.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Xiangqi%20Association%20(CXA)%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bcurrently%20impossible%20to%20prove%20that%20Yan%20engaged%20in%20cheating%20via%20'anal%20beads%2C'%26quot%3B%20but%20did%20say%20that%20the%20pooping%20part%20was%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYan%20consumed%20alcohol%20with%20others%20in%20his%20room%20on%20the%20night%20of%20the%2017th%2C%20and%20then%20he%20defecated%20in%20the%20bathtub%20of%20the%20room%20he%20was%20staying%20in%20on%20the%2018th%2C%20in%20an%20act%20that%20damaged%20hotel%20property%2C%20violated%20public%20order%20and%20good%20morals%2C%20had%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20the%20competition%20and%20the%20event%20of%20Xiangqi%2C%20and%20was%20of%20extremely%20bad%20character%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20association%20said%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fdec%2F27%2Fchinese-chess-champion-stripped-of-title-after-defecating-in-hotel-bathtub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CXA%20stripped%20Yan%20of%20his%20title%2C%20revoked%20his%20prize%20money%2C%20and%20banned%20him%20from%20playing%20for%20a%20year%2C%20the%20Global%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYan%20has%20since%20denied%20the%20allegations%2C%20claiming%20that%20he%20suffered%20from%20diarrhea%20after%20drinking%20alcohol%20and%20couldn't%20make%20it%20to%20the%20toilet%20in%20time%2C%20the%20Global%20Times%20reported%2C%20citing%20another%20Chinese%20outlet%2C%20Shangyou%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20the%20world%20of%20chess%20has%20been%20r