-hole-discovery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhile%20speaking%20to%20Science%20Friday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20non-profit%20science-education%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20simply%20too%20big%20too%20early.%20It's%20like%20looking%20in%20at%20a%20kindergarten%20classroom%20and%20there%20among%20all%20the%205-year-olds%20is%20one%20that%20is%20150%20pounds%20and%2For%20six%20feet%20tall%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Holz%2C%20a%20theorist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20who%20studies%20black%20holes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F24%2Fscience%2Fspace%2Fastronomy-black-holes.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPriya%20has%20found%20an%20extremely%20exciting%20black%20hole%2C%20if%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChandra%20X-ray%20Observatory%20first%20picked%20up%20the%20black%20hole%20by%20detecting%20X-rays%20let%20off%20by%20galaxy%20UHZ-1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20black%20hole%20inside%2C%20the%20observatory%20found%2C%20was%20a%20beast%20%E2%80%94%20estimated%20between%2010%20million%20and%20100%20million%20times%20as%20massive%20as%20the%20sun%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Farticle%2F2402016-astronomers-have-found-the-most-distant-black-hole-ever-confirmed%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20New%20Scientist%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20JWST%20set%20out%20to%20figure%20out%20where%20the%20black%20hole%20was%20located%2C%20scientists%20got%20a%20shock%3A%20it%20was%20inside%20UHZ-1%20about%2013.2%20billion%20light%20years%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20distance%20meant%20that%20this%20behemoth%20existed%20when%20the%20universe%20was%20very%20young%2C%20only%20about%20470%20million%20years%20after%20the%20Big%20Bang.%20It's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-black-hole-james-webb-space-telescope-discovery-early-universe-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurthest-flung%20black%20hole%20ever%20recorded%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20puzzling.%20One%20theory%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20supermassive%20black%20holes%20is%20that%20they%20come%20to%20be%20over%20a%20long%20time%2C%20The%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStars%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20universe%20were%20small%3A%20they%20burned%20what%20was%20available%2C%20hydrogen%20and%20helium%2C%20which%20means%20they%20flamed%20out%20quickly%2C%20leaving%20smaller%20black%20holes%20about%2010%20to%20100%20times%20bigger%20than%20the%20sun%20in%20their%20wake%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Fchandra%2Fnasa-telescopes-discover-record-breaking-black-hole%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20a%20press%20release%20from%20NASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20per%20this%20theory%2C%20black%20holes%20would%20merge%2C%20eventually%20forming%20supermassive%20black%20holes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20UHZ-1%20provides%20%26quot%3Bcompelling%20evidence%26quot%3B%20for%20another%20theory%2C%20said%20study%20author%20Natarajan%2C%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20astronomy%20and%20physics%20at%20Yale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20this%20theory%2C%20black%20holes%20could%20be%20born%20big%20from%20the%20get-go.%20This%20type%20of%20galaxy%2C%20a%20big%20black%20hole%20surrounded%20by%20a%20small%20cloud%20of%20gas%2C%20could%20provide%20a%20heavy%20%26quot%3Bseed%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20black%20hole%20that%20could%20grow%20into%20a%20supermassive%20black%20hole%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENatarajan%20and%20her%20colleagues%20have%20dubbed%20this%20type%20of%20cluster%20%26quot%3Bovermassive%20black%20hole%20galaxies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20supermassive%20black%20holes%2C%20then%2C%20wouldn't%20be%20born%20from%20early%20stars.%20The%20best%20explanation%20instead%2C%20per%20Natarajan%2C%20is%20that%20they%20came%20from%20cosmic%20gas%20collapsing%20in%20on%20itself%2C%20creating%20seeds%20already%20weighing%20between%20about%2010%2C000%20and%20100%2C000%20suns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20these%20start%20out%20in%20life%20overmassive%20implies%20that%20they%20will%20likely%20eventually%20evolve%20into%20supermassive%20black%20holes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Natarajan%2C%20speaking%20to%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNature%20does%20seem%20to%20make%20BH%20seeds%20many%20ways%2C%20beyond%20just%20stellar%20death!%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20confirm%20their%20theory%2C%20scientists%20will%20need%20more%20evidence%2C%20said%20Fabio%20Pacucci%20at%20the%20Harvard-Smithsonian%20Center%20for%20Astrophysics%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20per%20New%20Scientist.%20%26quot%3BIf%20this%20is%20at%20a%20100%20million%20solar%20masses%20it's%20pretty%20big%2C%20but%20if%20it's%20at%2010%20million%20solar%20masses%20it's%20not%20that%20big%2C%20so%20it%20could%20have%20possibly%20formed%20from%20a%20lighter%20seed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20hinges%20on%20finding%20more%20of%20these%20objects%2C%20possibly%20more%20massive%2C%20possibly%20at%20even%20higher%20distances%2C%20to%20really%20understand%20how%20the%20first%20population%20of%20black%20holes%20formed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20a%20peer-reviewed%20study%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dff418302a659d6b07cc975f5a9d7b724d6f9dc51cc04519b80294a719b8f802e%26postID%3D658befea8aa21447965669b2%26postSlug%3Dstrange-galaxy-spotted-nasa-may-rewrite-theory-black-holes-2023-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41550-023-02111-9%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejournal%20Nature%20Astronomy%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20November%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrang