s%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcolumbia-professor-carl-hart-legalize-drugs-heroin-for-grown-ups-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheroin%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%2010-year%20detour%20his%20life%20took%20after%20high%20school%20spanned%20all%20things%20concerning%20whether%20he%20would%20make%20it%20out%20of%20this%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStanding%20at%20the%20kitchen%20sink%20one%20summer%20morning%20in%202010%2C%20the%20warm%20prickle%20of%20hives%20took%20shape%20down%20my%20legs.%20Intense%20worry%20about%20my%20beautiful%20son%20and%20juggling%20his%20two%20little%20sisters%20was%20draining.%20The%20memory%20of%20our%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwoman-had-opioid-age-8-wants-parents-talk-openly-drugs-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Btalk%26quot%3B%20about%20drugs%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20age%209%20taunted%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20busy%20being%20the%20mom%20I%20wish%20I'd%20been.%20Overcompensating%20for%20every%20shortcoming%20of%20my%20first%20disastrous%2018-year-old%20go%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwoman-shares-how-becoming-a-mom-changed-all-her-relationships-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emotherhood%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20moved%20with%20his%20dad%20to%20Florida%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20ex%20moved%20his%20family%20from%20California%20to%20Florida%2C%20Bryant%20going%20wasn't%20a%20question.%20As%20a%20single%20secretary%2C%20deep%20in%20my%20own%20reverse%20adolescence%20with%20a%20million%20mistakes%20ahead%2C%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20learned%20Bryant%20was%20smoking%20marijuana%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe's%20in%20high%20school.%26quot%3B%20Kids%20experiment.%20He%20was%20a%20good%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEqual%20parts%20band%20nerd%20and%20cool%2C%20school%20came%20easily%20to%20Bryant.%20Bad%20knees%20and%20asthma%20sidelined%20him%20from%20sports%20beyond%20his%20two%20great%20loves%2C%20surfing%20and%20skateboarding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20a%20Bright%20Futures%20Scholarship%20to%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Florida%2C%20where%20he'd%20study%20electrical%20engineering.%20Engineers%20run%20in%20the%20family.%20We%20were%20excited%20for%20his%20next%20chapter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20started%20doing%20other%20drugs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20graduation%20looming%2C%20Bryant%2C%20a%20self-taught%20bass%20player%2C%20mentioned%20taking%20a%20gap%20year%20to%20tour%20with%20his%20band.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20his%20friends%20graduated%20from%20college%2C%20Bryant%20slipped%20deeper%20into%20addiction.%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20why.%20Had%20someone%20hurt%20him%3F%20Should%20we%20do%20therapy%20together%3F%20Was%20there%20something%20he%20was%20afraid%20to%20tell%20us%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20bright%2C%20sunny-dispositioned%20son%20was%20always%20working%20hard.%20Drugs%2C%20however%2C%20have%20a%20way%20of%20fucking%20things%20up%3B%20work%20ethic%20be%20damned.%20Cash%20from%20lucrative%20server%20and%20valet%20jobs%20went%20quickly%20when%20the%20pills%20ran%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20searched%2C%20like%20the%20bloodhound%20I%20am%2C%20for%20the%20doctor%20he%20mentioned%20prescribed%20him%20opiates%20for%20a%20mysterious%20shoulder%20injury%20and%20called.%20I%20felt%20surprise%20mixed%20with%20adrenaline%20when%20he%20answered.%20I%20told%20him%20to%20remember%20my%20name%20and%20threatened%20to%20call%20DEA%20friends%20if%20he%20ever%20wrote%20my%20son%20another%20prescription.%20In%202011%2C%20Cesar%20Deleon%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Farchive%2Fusao%2Ffls%2FPressReleases%2F2011%2F110518-02.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eindicted%20on%2055%20counts%20of%20illegal%20distribution%20of%20OxyCodone%20at%20his%20Lake%20Worth%20clinic%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20thought%20he%20would%20never%20stick%20a%20needle%20in%20his%20arm%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20never%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20kid%20would%20never%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%20because%20any%20kid%20might.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20watched%20helplessly%20as%20Bryant's%20world%20disintegrated.%20Weeks%20turned%20into%20months%20that%20we%20wouldn't%20hear%20from%20him.%20Relief%20at%20finally%20hearing%20his%20voice%20turned%20quickly%20to%20despair%20when%20it%20came%20from%20jail.%20There%20was%20talk%20of%20rehab%2C%20which%20I%20argued%20passionately%20would%20be%20a%20waste%20of%20money.%20He%20wasn't%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20move%20north%20to%20live%20with%20me%20to%20get%20clean%20started%20well.%20High%20on%20hope%2C%20we%20went%20directly%20from%20the%20airport%20to%20a%20Narcotics%20Anonymous%20meeting.%20The%20rule%20was%20daily%20meetings.%20When%20he%20got%20high%20with%20people%20he%20met%20there%20%E2%80%94%20a%20cruel%20but%20common%20irony%2C%20it%20was%20devastating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20had%20a%20one-strike%20rule.%20There%20is%20a%20specific%20kind%20of%20pain%20attached%20to%20the%20act%20of%20kicking%20Bryant%20out%20of%20my%20home%20at%20one%20of%20his%20lowest%20moments.%20The%20following%20handful%20of%20years%20were%20his%20darkest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20he%20met%20a%20girl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EShe%20helped%20him%20through%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20the%20spark%2C%20but%20Bryant%20did%20the%20hardest%20part.%20She%20housed%20and%20supported%20him%20in%20every%20way.%20In%20Bryant's%20eyes%2C%20she%20was%20there%20when%20his%20family%20abandoned%20him.%20I%20get%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20family%2C%20we%20had%20to%20make%20him%20choose%20between%20us%20and%20drugs.%20There%20was%20zero%20pleasure%20in%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20there%20was%20a%20wedding.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20I%20watched%20Bryant%20graduate%20magna%20cum%20laude%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20electrical%20engineering%20from%20FAU.%20He%20was%20also%20inducted%20into%20Tau%20Beta%20Pi%2C%20the%20most%20prestigious%20engineering%20honor%20society%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Bryant%20became%20a%20father%20and%2C%20after%20years%20of%20perseverance%2C%20landed%20his%20dream%20job%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20encouraged%20this%20essay%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20did%20work%20hard%2C%20but%20I%20never%20would%20have%20survived%20if%20it%20were%20not%20for%20about%20a%20thousand%20acts%20of%20kindness%20by%20others%2C%20both%20in%20active%20addiction%20and%20recovery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryant%20is%20an%20incredible%2C%20big-hearted%20human%20with%20so%20much%20empathy%20for%20the%20world%20around%20him.%20His%20journey%20through%20the%20hell%20of%20addiction%20has%20created%20a%20vast%20scope%20of%20gratitude%20for%20what%20is%20and%20what%20will%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fson-drug-abuse-heroin-addiction-recovery-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703675521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f5a2b7a3c8094d5d9bcdb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fson-drug-abuse-heroin-addiction-recovery-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20mom%20says%20her%20son%20battled%20a%20decade-long%20drug%20addiction%2C%20and%20she%20worried%20he%20wasn't%20going%20to%20recover.%20Now%2C%20he's%20thriving%20and%20raising%20a%20family.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jennifer%20Cannon)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fson-drug-abuse-heroin-addiction-recovery-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We're%20getting%20closer%20to%20OpenAI's%20first%20device%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jony%20ives%20and%20sam%20altman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65145c201c099d0019ad3e49%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500