work%20meetings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224819%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20people%20in%20a%20meeting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6585a6ffa79e5746976ca611%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222990%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWednesday%20was%20the%20most%20popular%20day%20for%20work%20meetings%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20Calendly.%3Cp%3ERudzhan%20Nagiev%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWednesday%20took%20the%20top%20spot%20for%20meetings%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Calendly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20maker%20of%20scheduling%20software%20said%20about%C2%A0a%20quarter%20of%20meetings%20took%20place%20from%207%20p.m.%20to%208%20p.m.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeetings%20have%20value%20but%20too%20many%20can%20endanger%20our%20ability%20to%20do%20good%20work%2C%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20many%20meetings%20might%20be%20putting%20the%20hump%20in%20your%20Hump%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurns%20out%20Wednesday%20was%20the%20most%20popular%20day%20for%20work%20meetings%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0virtually%20or%20IRL%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Calendly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20midweek%20work-a-thon%20probably%20isn't%20a%20big%20surprise%20given%20the%20dearth%20of%20people%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmondays-fridays-dead-return-to-office-landlord-wfh-rto-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eroll%20into%20the%20office%20on%20Mondays%20and%20Fridays%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20virtual-only%20meetings%2C%20Tuesday%20took%20the%20top%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20more%20surprising%20is%20that%20there%20were%20fewer%20meetings%20on%20weekends%20this%20year%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20a%20relief%20to%20anyone%20who's%20ever%20been%20on%20a%20client%20call%20when%20they'd%20otherwise%20be%20scoping%20out%20brunch%20spots%20or%20running%20errands.%20In-person%20meetings%20on%20Saturdays%20dropped%2017%25%20in%202023%20from%202021%20while%20those%20meetings%20fell%2029%25%20on%20Sundays%20over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20Calendly%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%2C%20pulled%20in%20early%20December%2C%20are%20drawn%20from%20more%20than%2020%20million%20users%20of%20the%20company's%20scheduling%20software.%20About%20half%20of%20Calendly%20users%20are%20based%20outside%20the%20US.%20The%20findings%20were%20a%20mix%20of%20the%20mundane%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0morning%20meetings%20aren't%20popular%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20unexpected%3A%20Nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20in-person%20or%20virtual%20meetings%20took%20place%20between%207%20p.m.%20and%208%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20time%20it%20happens%2C%20all%20of%20this%20togetherness%20can%20add%20to%20worker%20stress.%20There%20are%20hacks%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-burnout-google-singapore-executive-meetings-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einoculate%20against%20meeting%20overload%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20canceling%20all%20meetings%20isn't%20advisable%20because%20they're%20often%20essential%2C%20Ron%20Hetrick%2C%20senior%20labor%20economist%20at%20the%20research%20firm%20Lightcast%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20rip%20on%20meetings%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there's%20a%20value%20in%20meetings.%26quot%3B%20Hetrick%20said%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20younger%20ones%20still%20learning%20their%20way%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0are%20forced%20to%20mature%20and%20to%20hear%20people%20disagree.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20seeing%20how%20problems%20get%20worked%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20that%20problem-solving%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20afternoon%20and%20early%20evening.%20Some%2086%25%20of%20meetings%20took%20place%20from%202%20p.m.%20to%206%20p.m.%2C%20Calendly%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20staying%20on%20till%20late%20in%20the%20workday%2C%20there's%20evidence%20that%20more%20of%20us%20might%20be%20trading%20our%20Sweetgreen%20for%20slide%20decks.%20Calendly%20said%20meetings%20from%2011%20a.m.%20to%201%20p.m.%20jumped%2048%25%20in%202023%20from%202021.%20Those%20meetings%20could%20include%20a%20meal%2C%20of%20course%2C%20though%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-skip-lunch-break-meetings-too-much-work-2023-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGen%2520Z%2520workers%2520are%2520most%2Cat%2520least%2520once%2520a%2520week.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eskipping%20lunch%20is%20something%20some%20Gen%20Z%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20reported%20doing.%20In%20part%2C%20it's%20because%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20worry%20than%20their%20older%20colleagues%20that%20the%20boss%20will%20disapprove%20of%20a%20lunch%20break%2C%20according%20to%20BI's%20prior%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20piece%20of%20advice%20for%20people%20who%20hate%20on%20meetings%3A%20Make%20them%20virtual.%20Calendly%20found%20that%20about%20half%20of%20remote%20meetings%20are%20wrapped%20up%20in%2030%20minutes%20compared%20with%20only%2031%25%20of%20in-person%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalendly%20said%20more%20of%20its%20users%20are%20slapping%20daily%20limits%20on%20their%20%3Cspan%3Eget-togethers%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20The%20average%20cap%3A%20six%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20meetings%20can%20have%20value%2C%20too%20many%20on%20the%20calendar%20can%20make%20us%20overly%20focused%20on%20checking%20off%20tasks%20and%20less%20willing%20to%20collaborate%2C%20Andr%C3%A9%20Martin%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BWrong%20Fit%2C%20Right%20Fit%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI.%20This%20might%20mean%20we%20skip%20asking%20about%20coworkers'%20days%20or%20how%20we%20might%20help%20them%20solve%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20danger%20of%20giving%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20those%20things%20that%20allow%20us%20to%20have%20kind%20of%20the%20depth%20of%20relationship%20we%20need%20to%20do%20really%20good%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20calendar%20is%20bursting%20with%20meetings%2C%20it%20also%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20change%20gears%20from%20one%20to%20the%20next%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0what%20Martin%20calls%20context%20shifting.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20go%20back-to-back-to-back.%20We're%20terrible%20at%20context%20shifting%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20get%20to%20the%20backend%20of%20this%20meeting%2C%20and%20I%20go%20into%20the%20next%20one%2C%20I%20spend%20the%20first%2015%20minutes%20just%20trying%20to%20find%20my%20feet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwednesday-most-popular-day-work-meetings-avoid-overload-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703673781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6585a699a79e5746976ca5b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwednesday-most-popular-day-work-meetings-avoid-overload-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wednesday%20was%20the%20most%20popular%20day%20for%20work%20meetings%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Calendly.%20And%20more%20users%20capped%20the%20number%20at%20six%20per%20day.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwednesday-most-popular-day-work-meetings-avoid-overload-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tamannaah-Vijay%20Varma%20jet%20off%20for%20New%20Year%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703673623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106321517%2Cimgsize-50754.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi