%20almost%20a%20ritual%20for%20Hindi%20film%20fans%20every%20few%20years.%20The%20production%20house%20burst%20onto%20the%20scene%20with%20%3Cem%3EDil%20Chahta%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2001)%20%E2%80%93%20following%20three%20friends%20from%20their%20early%2020s%20to%20their%20late%2020s%3B%20and%20then%20followed%20it%20up%20with%20%3Cem%3EZindagi%20Na%20Milegi%20Dobara%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20which%20was%20set%20around%20three%20childhood%20friends%20making%20good%20on%20a%20college%20pact%20in%20their%2030s.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20production%20house%2C%20coupled%20with%20Zoya%20Akhtar%20and%20Reema%20Kagti%E2%80%99s%20Tiger%20Baby%20Films%2C%20tells%20a%20tale%20of%20three%20friends%20navigating%20their%20double%20lives%20in%20the%20social%20media%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20movies%20are%20usually%20set%20in%20an%20upper-middle%20class%20neighbourhood%2C%20amongst%20those%20not%20struggling%20for%20their%20basic%20needs.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20relaxed%20vibe%20in%20these%20films%2C%20as%20an%20eclectic%20group%20of%20musicians%20make%20up%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20soundtrack%20to%20play%20through%20montages%2C%20and%20characters%20try%20to%20find%20out%20what%20it%20all%20really%20means.%20Both%20Farhan%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20film%20and%20Zoya%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20film%20conclude%20with%20life-altering%20epiphanies%3A%20some%20friendships%20survive%20everything%2C%20or%20how%20road%20trips%20can%20bring%20catharsis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArjun%20Varain%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20tries%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20a%20generation%20that%E2%80%99s%20addicted%20to%20consuming%20other%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20and%20how%20they%20slowly%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20lies%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FE1da2YxROaw%3Fsi%3DYqm6kTZTAmGKkQ5j%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20fertile%20premise%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20is%20full%20of%20(self)%20deception%2C%20given%20how%20so%20much%20is%20left%20unsaid%20in%20everyday%20life.%20At%20first%20we%20were%20only%20subject%20to%20people%E2%80%99s%20thoughts%20if%20they%20spoke%20to%20us%2C%20but%20now%20they%20reach%20us%20in%20the%20manner%20of%20pictures%2C%20screenshots%2C%20tweets%2C%20threads%2C%20Facebook%20posts.%20Also%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20way%20for%20us%20to%20actively%20peek%20into%20other%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20even%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20actively%20following%20them.%20Everyone%20wants%20to%20project%20how%20%E2%80%9Chumbled%E2%80%9D%20they%20are%20to%20be%20living%20their%20%E2%80%9Cbest%20lives%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20rarely%20the%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDebutante%20director%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20its%20strongest%20and%20most%20distinct%2C%20when%20it%20depicts%20a%20generation%E2%80%99s%20obsession%20with%20their%20smartphones.%20Our%20entire%20lives%20are%20now%20gamified%20in%20the%20manner%20where%20popularity%20can%20be%20quantified%20through%20a%20dozen%20metrics%3A%20likes%2C%20reactions%2C%20retweets%2C%20followers%2C%20views%2C%20subscribers%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20follows%20three%20friends%20in%20their%2020s%20%E2%80%93%20Imaad%20(Siddhant%20Chaturvedi)%2C%20Ahana%20(Ananya%20Panday)%20and%20Neil%20(Adarsh%20Gourav).%20Imaad%20is%20the%20son%20of%20a%20rich%20businessman%2C%20currently%20pursuing%20his%20dream%20of%20becoming%20a%20stand-up%20comic.%20Neil%2C%20from%20a%20middle-class%20Catholic%20home%2C%20is%20a%20physical%20trainer%20in%20the%20proximity%20of%20Bandra%E2%80%99s%20wealth%20and%20privilege.%20Ahana%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20one%20among%20the%20three%20to%20be%20in%20a%20stable%20relationship%20and%20have%20a%20full-time%20job%2C%20comes%20fully%20undone%20when%20her%20boyfriend%20suddenly%20breaks%20up%20with%20her%2C%20without%20giving%20her%20any%20closure%20about%20why%20he%E2%80%99s%20dumping%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20friends%20are%20dependent%20on%20social%20media%20to%20varying%20degrees.%20Imaad%20needs%20to%20go%20%E2%80%98viral%E2%80%99%20for%20his%20shows%20to%20start%20filling%20up%2C%20Neil%E2%80%99s%20gym%20has%20celebrity%20clients%20like%20Malaika%20Arora%20Khan%20and%20Farhan%20Akhtar%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20social%20media%20following%20will%20expedite%20his%20journey%20to%20becoming%20a%20known%20celebrity%20trainer%2C%20and%20open%20his%20own%20gym.%20After%20Ahana%E2%80%99s%20break-up%2C%20she%20gets%20her%20revenge%20by%20curating%20a%20%E2%80%98happy%E2%80%99%20social%20media%20feed%20to%20get%20the%20attention%20of%20her%20ex-boyfriend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%E2%80%99s%20strong%20observation%20skills%20show%20up%20early%20in%20the%20film%2C%20when%20we%20see%20the%20three%20friends%20sitting%20in%20the%20same%20room%2C%20their%20faces%20lit%20by%20the%20glow%20of%20their%20respective%20phones%2C%20laptops.%20There%20are%20other%20scenes%20too%2C%20where%20Singh%20documents%20his%20characters%E2%80%99%20sudden%20changes%20in%20mood%20after%20a%20bad%20day%2C%20once%20they%20see%20notifications%20on%20their%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20only%20when%20the%20friends%20come%20together%20to%20open%20a%20business%2C%20is%20when%20the%20film%20begins%20to%20take%20the%20convenient%20narrative%20route.%20It%20takes%20only%20a%20few%20questions%20for%20Neil%20to%20convince%20Ahana%20to%20quit%20her%20job%20to%20make%20a%20business%20plan%20for%20his%20gym%2C%20while%20Imaad%20agrees%20to%20invest%20his%20inheritance%20into%20it%20merely%20two%20lines%20later.%20The%20film%E2%80%99s%20primary%20conflict%20%E2%80%93%20the%20confrontation%20between%20Imaad%20and%20Neil%2C%20after%20the%20former%20makes%20some%20unsavoury%20jokes%20on%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20an%20influencer%2C%20Lala%20(Anya%20Singh)%20%E2%80%93%20appears%20slightly%20underwritten.%20I%20found%20it%20a%20little%20hard%20to%20digest%20that%20a%20stand-up%20comic%20would%20go%20on%20stage%20and%20say%20those%20things%20about%20a%20close%20friend%2C%20especially%20with%20him%20sitting%20in%20the%20audience%2C%20without%20giving%20him%20a%20heads-up%20about%20it.%20Even%20though%20both%20Chaturvedi%20and%20Gourav%20are%20solid%20actors%2C%20who%20do%20their%20best%20to%20sell%20this%20confrontation%20slowly%20escalating%20with%20each%20line%2C%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20think%20how%20the%20scene%20needed%20a%20moment%E2%80%99s%20pause%20before%20it%20to%20make%20it%20truly%20impactful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20really%20enjoyed%20the%20ease%20between%20Imaad%20and%20Simran%20(Kalki%20Koechlin)%2C%20a%20grieving%20photographer%2C%20who%20meets%20him%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20a%20project.%20Both%20Chaturvedi%20and%20Koechlin%20are%20secure%20actors%2C%20and%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20truly%20exist%20in%20a%20scene%20without%20any%20off-screen%20baggage.%20Gourav%20is%20a%20very%20fine%20actor%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20emoting%20with%20body%20language.%20The%20way%20his%20body%20shrinks%2C%20when%20a%20client%20of%20his%20tells%20him%20to%20not%20%E2%80%98cross%20the%20line%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20exemplary.%20Also%2C%20his%20run-ins%20with%20his%20conservative%20father%20(Vijay%20Maurya%2C%20feasting%20on%20these%20tiny%20roles%20in%20Excel%20movies)%2C%20who%20tries%20to%20warn%20him%20about%20his%20boundless%20(and%20sometimes%20reckless)%20ambition.%20It%20might%20not%20be%20saying%20much%20after%20all%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20these%20films%20are%20tailor-made%20for%20Panday.%20She%E2%80%99s%20not%20been%20the%20most%20promising%20actor%20around%20since%20she%20made%20her%20debut%20nearly%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20she%20makes%20a%20compelling%20case%20for%20herself%20in%20at%20least%20two%20scenes%20in%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20keeps%20us%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20given%20how%20sincere%20and%20easy%20it%20is.%20But%20it%20slowly%20tapers%20off%20towards%20the%20end%20without%20fully%20maximising%20its%20potential.%20A%20track%20around%20Neil%20and%20his%20influencer%20girlfriend%20feels%20tentative%2C%20with%20the%20makers%20trying%20to%20balance%20her%20artifice%2C%20while%20also%20trying%20to%20humanise%20her.%20The%20track%20concludes%20with%20a%20voice-over%20doling%20out%20platitudes%20about%20Neil%E2%80%99s%20bad%20behaviour%2C%20which%20feels%20like%20a%20hurried%2C%20lazy%20way%20to%20wrap%20things%20up.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20towards%20the%20end%20when%20Imaad%20owns%20up%20to%20his%20demons%20from%20the%20past%20by%20announcing%20it%20in%20his%20set%20to%20an%20audience.%20It%20feels%20awkwardly%20written%2C%20and%20performed%20by%20an%20unusually%20stiff%20Chaturvedi%2C%20given%20how%20he%E2%80%99s%20free-flowing%20in%20most%20other%20scenes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArjun%20Varain%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20the%20rare%20Hindi%20film%20that%20seems%20to%20understand%20the%20lies%20of%20social%20media%2C%20but%20unfortunately%20chooses%20to%20not%20cut%20too%20deep.%20While%20it%20results%20in%20a%20respectable%2C%20watchable%20debut%2C%20it%20never%20quite%20ascends%20to%20becoming%20a%20document%20of%20a%20whole%20generation.%20It%E2%80%99s%20ultimately%20sad%20that%20for%20its%20commentary%20on%20social%20media%2C%20%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20the%20recall%20value%20of%20an%20Insta%20reel.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703658892000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F27120951%2Fimage-1675.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkho-gaye-hum-kahan-starts-strong-but-settles-with-the-recall-value-of-an-insta-reel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20more%20film%20abou